n-k
\frac{1}{n-k}
P(n)
 \begin{align} P &=\frac2n+\sum_{k=2}^{n-2} \frac{2(n-k)}{n(n-1)}\cdot\frac{1}{n-k}\\ &=\frac2n+\sum_{k=2}^{n-2}\frac{2}{n(n-1)} \\ &=\frac2n+\frac{2(n-3)}{n(n-1)} \\ &=\frac{2(n-1)}{n(n-1)}+\frac{2(n-3)}{n(n-1)} \\ &=\frac{2\bigl((n-1)+(n-3)\bigr)}{n(n-1)} \\ &=\frac{4(n-2)}{n(n-1)} \\ \end{align} 
4m+8+4(m-3) = 8m-4 = 4(n-2)
\frac{4(n-2)}{n(n-1)}
